    <note>Hu(1) Cong [18851] When the Mongol armies arrived at Changzhou, his son Yingyan [18853] was made Jiedu panguan by the prefect and planned the defense of the city. Cong, Yingyan and Yingyan's elder brother, Yingfa [18852], all agreed to die in defense of the state. The youngest brother, son #3, Yingdeng [18854], was ordered to save his life in order to preserve the clan sacrifices (zongji). CBD, 2, 1580.</note>
